label sweven_mirror_intro:
    scene sweven_mirror with bgwipe
    show ingram with dissolve
    "He gestures toward the large mirror near the corner of the cafe. Its surface glows faintly with Lunaria light."
    ingram "If your heart is ready, the mirror will open the path."
    uk_generic "...I want to see her. Just once more."
    ingram "Then let's begin."
    "Ingram stands and guides the man toward the mirror. The air around them starts to shimmer as the Lunaria essence reacts."
    "He instructs the man to focus on the memory while keeping his heart open. The mirror brightens, and the man’s reflection begins to blur."
    "Within moments, his figure fades into the light until he disappears entirely into the mirror’s surface."
    "Ingram remains still, concentrating, his eyes fixed on the mirror."
    "After a few moments, the glow starts to fade, returning the room to normal."
    ingram "...And that completes the first part of the guiding process."
    emi "So... he’s inside the memory now?"
    ingram "Yes. The mirror constructs a dream from the memory they chose. I help them navigate it—make peace with what they need to. When that’s done, the spirit moves on."
    emi "...He was a spirit, wasn’t he?"
    ingram "He was. A new arrival. They often come here first—drawn by what they miss most."
    emi "And that drink helped him remember?"
    ingram "Exactly. The drink reflects the memory their heart yearns for. It lets them face it, understand it, and find peace before moving on."
    "He gestures to the faint glow still lingering in the empty cup."
    return